{
  "stem": "11611.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The war was an outbreak, in part, of American demands on Japan, with threats that we'd cut off their oil supplies and other-- other supplies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't think anybody except people who were really much more knowledgeable than I was expected the war to break out then.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were some indications that relations between Japan and the United States were not very good at that time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, historically, the Japanese had tied themselves up in the so-called 'axis' with Germany and Italy, the so-called anti-democratic forces.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I entered in April, but I think I was signed up by January or February.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'42.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because the Navy was running a Japanese language school, and that's what I entered.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Boulder, Colorado, attached to the University of Colorado.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's hard to say what it was like.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was six hours a day of Japanese classes, three, four hours of studying Japanese, strenuous efforts and very little production.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was true not only for me but for most of the class.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were a handful of people in the class who had a real affinity for studying languages who very quickly developed either some spoken or written skills.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in fact, in the post-war period, all of the key translators of Japanese literature, classic and modern, were classmates of mine in the Navy Japanese Language School.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in retrospect, I went to a reunion of the Japanese Language School of the Navy, and I have a son who lives in Boulder who said, what kind of crazy project was that?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why would you ever go study Japanese when the United States had literally tens of thousands of Nisei with Japanese background who could speak Japanese?",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
